Program: Outlook
Title: Violence in Brazil
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbrzv
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
100 people died in violence involving prisoners in Brazil, a prison guard speaks out. Also, the changing place of women in society. Artist and filmmaker Hugues de Montalembert talks about the attack in 1978 which blinded him. The importance of chopsticks in China and why a tax is being introduced. The university student who has been studying for 12 years and keeps putting off graduation. Presenter: Heather Payton. Show less